\b Assigned Complaint List - Architecture\b0\par
Complaint Management System\par
\par

\b 1. Purpose\b0\par
Assigned Complaint List shows complaints assigned to the logged-in user (Dealer / Engineer). From this list, the user can open Service Update to add Installed Base and Service Log for the complaint.\par
\par

\b 2. Main Files\b0\par
\bullet  dse_lse_complaint_list.php - assigned complaint list and actions\par
\bullet  service_update_complaint.php - service update save handler\par
\bullet  includes/complaint_datatable_helpers.php - grid helpers and permissions\par
\bullet  includes/complaint_service_log_helpers.php - service update and service log link\par
\bullet  includes/complaint_service_log_modal.php - Service Update popup\par
\bullet  api/assigned_complaints_datatable.php - grid data\par
\bullet  api/complaint_service_log_prefill.php - prefill for service log from complaint\par
\bullet  api/complaint_service_log_summary.php - service log summary in popup\par
\par

\b 3. Shared Components\b0\par
\bullet  complaint_status_cards.php - status filter cards\par
\bullet  complaint_service_update_save_helpers.php - service update save logic\par
\bullet  complaint_service_log_draft_helpers.php - draft service log from complaint\par
\bullet  complaint_service_update_service_log.js - Service Update UI\par
\bullet  rbac_access_helpers.php - permissions\par
\par

\b 4. Basic Flow\b0\par
\bullet  User opens Assigned Complaint List\par
\bullet  Grid loads assigned records from complaints and complaint_assignments\par
\bullet  User opens Service Update for a complaint\par
\bullet  User can add Installed Base if needed, then add Service Log\par
\bullet  After Installed Base save, user returns to Service Update on same complaint\par
\bullet  Service Log draft can be saved and later completed\par
\par

\b 5. Database\b0\par
Main tables: complaints, complaint_assignments\par
Related tables: service_logs, installed_base, complaint_closures\par
\par

\b 6. Permissions\b0\par
RBAC module: assigned-complaint-list (view, service-update)\par
}
